App-BCVI-NotifyClient

This module is a plugin for 'bcvi' (see: http://search.cpan.org/dist/App-BCVI).
To use it, simply copy the NotifyClient.pm file to your $HOME/.config/bcvi/
folder.

The role of this plugin is to send messages back to the user's workstation for
display through the Desktop notifictation system.  It is assumed you have
installed another plugin (e.g.: App-BCVI-NotifyDesktop) to handle the GUI
notifications.


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

You can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

Before installation:

    perldoc lib/App/BCVI/NotifyClient.pm

After instalation:

    perldoc $HOME/.config/bcvi/NotifyClient.pm

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=App-BCVI-NotifyClient

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/App-BCVI-NotifyClient

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/App-BCVI-NotifyClient

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/App-BCVI-NotifyClient


